---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base
  title="Log In to IncomeRecord.com"
  description="Log in to your IncomeRecord.com account to access your saved pay stub history, employer profiles, and settings. Free accounts available -- no credit card required."
  canonical="https://incomerecord.com/login"
>
  <main class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <div class="max-w-md mx-auto mb-16">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Log In to IncomeRecord.com</h1>
      <p class="text-gray-600 mb-8">Access your saved stubs and account settings.</p>

      <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-8 shadow-sm">
        <div class="mb-4 p-4 bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg">
          <p class="text-blue-800 text-sm"><strong>Note:</strong> Account features (stub history, saved employers) are coming soon with the Pro tier. The free generator at <a href="/" class="underline">incomerecord.com</a> works without an account right now.</p>
        </div>

        <form class="space-y-4" action="#" method="POST">
          <div>
            <label for="email" class="block text-sm font-medium text-gray-700 mb-1">Email address</label>
            <input
              type="email"
              id="email"
              name="email"
              autocomplete="email"
              placeholder="you@example.com"
              class="w-full px-4 py-3 border border-gray-300 rounded-lg focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500 focus:border-transparent"
            />
          </div>

          <div>
            <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-1">
              <label for="password" class="block text-sm font-medium text-gray-700">Password</label>
              <a href="/forgot-password" class="text-sm text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-700">Forgot password?</a>
            </div>
            <input
              type="password"
              id="password"
              name="password"
              autocomplete="current-password"
              placeholder="Your password"
              class="w-full px-4 py-3 border border-gray-300 rounded-lg focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500 focus:border-transparent"
            />
          </div>

          <button
            type="submit"
            class="w-full bg-blue-600 text-white py-3 rounded-lg font-semibold hover:bg-blue-700 transition-colors"
          >
            Log In
          </button>
        </form>

        <p class="text-center text-gray-600 mt-6 text-sm">
          Don't have an account?
          <a href="/signup" class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-700 font-medium">Sign up free</a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <section class="border-t border-gray-200 pt-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">What You Can Do Once Logged In</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-8 max-w-2xl">When account features launch with our Pro tier, logging in will unlock several time-saving features for people who generate pay stubs regularly.</p>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Stub History</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Every pay stub you generate gets saved automatically to your account. Access any previous stub at any time — re-download it, use it as the basis for a new stub, or share it via a secure link.</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">This matters most when you're in the middle of a rental application or loan process and suddenly need a stub from three months ago that you didn't save. With history enabled, it's always there.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Saved Employer Profiles</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Save your employer's name, address, and EIN so you don't retype them every time. If you generate pay stubs for multiple clients or companies, save each as a separate profile and switch between them with one click.</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Small business owners who generate stubs for their employees find this especially useful — set up each employer once, generate stubs for multiple employees without re-entering company information.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Employee Preset Profiles (Pro)</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Save employee information including name, address, filing status, and standard deductions. Generating a new stub for an existing employee becomes two clicks: select the employee, enter the gross pay and period dates, generate.</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Particularly useful for contractors or gig workers who generate stubs at regular intervals — once your profile is set up, each new stub takes seconds.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Account Settings and Security</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Manage your email address, update your password, and control your notification preferences. For Pro subscribers, manage your subscription and billing from the account dashboard.</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Your account information is protected with industry-standard security practices. We never store payment card information — that's handled by our payment processor.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-12 bg-gray-50 rounded-xl p-8">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Need a Pay Stub Right Now?</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">The free generator doesn't require a login. If you need a pay stub immediately, you can generate one without creating an account.</p>
      <a href="/" class="inline-block bg-blue-600 text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-lg font-semibold hover:bg-blue-700 transition-colors">Generate a Pay Stub Free</a>
    </section>
  </main>
</Base>
